Class Kernel

  • java.lang.Object
    • Kernel

  • public class Kernel
extends java.lang.Object
    A non-dynamic, three-dimensional kernel, with floating point data. A kernel is a 3D convolution matrix that describes a filtering algorithm on a 3D dataset. The dimensions should be mxnxp, where m, n, and p are odd numbers: m,n,p = 2k+1 for all k. The major dimension is the Z dimension; that is, the data is stored as [Z][X][Y] (depth, width, height) and input data arrays are expected in this format.

      • normalize

        public void normalize()
        Normalize the kernel. Normalize ensures that the sum of the entire kernel is 1, which is nice when doing certain image filtering operations such as blurring or sharpening (normalized kernels ensure the overall brightness of the image stays mostly constant).

      • getHalfWidth

        public int getHalfWidth()
        Get the "half-width" of the kernel, which is (width-1)/2. For sane kernels (which have an odd width), this is the number of pixels on each side of the center.
        Returns:
        The "half-width" of the kernel

      • getHalfHeight
